nodes.documentation:
Ownable
The Ownable contract has an owner address, and provides basic authorization control
functions, this simplifies the implementation of "user permissions".
nodes.name: Ownable

nodes.documentation: The Ownable constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender
Throws if called by any account other than the owner.
nodes.name: onlyOwner

nodes.documentation: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.
